RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $2,000 Or Less Not Consider ed In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NENE ROMANO broke out, weaved early and bumped with AROUSING LOVER, contested pace three wide on the backstretch, shook clear early on the turn, entered lane clear, kept to task and won with a diminishing margin. AUNTIE BEV vied for lead along the inside with a pair of rivals, continued to hold the rail on the turn, entered lane in range and kept to task, and gained on leader to the wire. LADY RANGER vied in between rivals for the lead on the backstretch, continued two wide most of the turn, unable to match strides with top two in the lane, but kept on to hold show. ASYLUM stalked trio of leaders on the backstretch, continued to save ground throughout and bested the rest while never threatening to improve. COUSIN NIECEY stalked trio of leaders in between rivals on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn and failed to rally in the lane. FOR MY BROTHER reared and came away slow, cantered along after losing all chance and never threatened. AROUSING LOVER bumped by weaving rival exiting the chute, kept well of the rail on the backstretch, took turn four wide and kept wide through the turn, and came up empty approaching the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Ranger
ENTRY.OWNER: Garcia Juan Manuel Salgado Carlos Abel Torres Gustavo Alejandro and Zubieta Lore
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, kept on, held show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. CLAIM.OWNER: Saratoga West Ortega Jr Alex and Ortega Vincent

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHASING THE VISION sent clear, opened up on the backstretch, continued clear on the turn, almost headed into the lane, responded and dug in to repel bid to win clear. DIVINELY DIVERSE tracked clear leader off the rail on the backstretch, continued to track on the turn, ranged up with a menacing bid heading into the lane, rival dug in and repelled the bid by DIVINELY DIVERSE. SHARP WARNING showed better speed with the addition of blinkers, tracked leader along the inside, continued to save ground on the turn and kept on in the lane while never threatening top two. HOLYJAZZ stalked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, and bested rest in the lane. HELICOPTER PILOT stalked pace along the inside on the backstretch, continued to save ground on the turn and came up empty in the lane. MONGOLIAN MOON settled well off the pace and off the rail on the backstretch, continued to trail on the turn and came up empty in the lane. MISSING MAURICE settled well off the pace three wide, never threatened and tired in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Chasing the Vision
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent clear, met bid, repelled foe
